# Platform Rules

You are working in `platform-core`, the reusable infrastructure layer for a multi-tenant relationship-commerce platform.

Famm is the first application on this platform. It is not the platform itself.

Before architecture, schema, API, or feature decisions, read:

`platform-docs/docs/constitution/PLATFORM_CONSTITUTION.md`

## Layer classification

Classify every change as one of:

- Platform Core
- Application Layer
- User Experience Layer

Platform Core belongs in this repo. Famm-specific logic belongs in `famm-app`.

## Platform primitives

Prefer these primitives before creating new entities:

- User
- Organization
- Community
- Relationship
- Activity
- Offer
- Transaction
- Conversation
- Referral
- Affiliate
- CalendarEvent
- ReputationSignal

## Required rules

1. Do not introduce fitness-specific concepts (trainer, client, workout, gym, session, package, membership) unless an ADR explicitly approves it.
2. All tenant-sensitive models must include tenant ownership (`organization_id` or `tenant_id`).
3. All major business actions must emit domain events.
4. APIs must represent reusable platform capabilities, not screen-specific workflows.
5. If a change only benefits Famm, implement it in `famm-app` instead.

## Review prompts

Before changing architecture, run `.ai/prompts/platform-review.md`.

Before changing data models, run `.ai/prompts/data-model-review.md`.

Before opening a pull request, run `.ai/prompts/pr-review.md`.

## Naming

- Use `calendar-event` for the scheduled occurrence primitive folder to avoid confusion with domain events.
- Use industry-neutral names in platform-core (`provider`, `customer`, `activity`, `offer`).
- Application labels (e.g. "trainer") are allowed only at the app/UI layer.
